/-!
# The span of a set of vectors, as a submodule

* `Submodule.span s` is defined to be the smallest submodule containing the set `s`.

## Notation

* We introduce the notation `R έΙβ v` for the span of a singleton, `Submodule.span R {v}`.  This is
  `\span`, not the same as the scalar multiplication `έΑλ`/`\bub`.

-/

@[expose] public section

assert_not_exists Field

variable {R RέΓΓ K M MέΓΓ V S : Type*}

namespace Submodule

open Function Set

